.TH WindowMenuPost 3X
.SH NAME
\*LWindowMenuPost \*O\(em Command to post the window menu
.SH SYNOPSIS
\*LWindowMenuPost\*O
\*VWidgetName\*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
\*LWindowMenuPost\*O
command will post the window menu on the window associated with 
\*VWidgetName\*O.
If
\*VWidgetName\*O
is not a shell with its own window on the display, the window
of the nearest shell parent in the widget hierarchy will be used.
This function is executed by moving the pointer to the systemMenu
button of the window, and generating a Select button press.
.IP "\*VWidgetName\*O" 14n
The XtName of the widget to be acted upon.
.PP
For more information about \*LWindowMenuPost\*O, see
the \*EOSF/Motif Quality Assurance Test Suite User's Guide\*O.
.SH EXAMPLE
\*LWindowMenuPost Shell1\*O
.PP
This command will move the pointer to the systemMenu button on the window
associated with \*LShell1\*O 
and generate a Select button press, thereby posting the
window menu.
.SH "RELATED INFORMATION"
